            . I am a <rs id="t18320517-227-viclabel1317" type="occupation">carpenter</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320517-227-victim1725 t18320517-227-viclabel1317"></join>. The prisoner lodged with me in April - I went into the workshop when he left, and found three duplicates; I then looked over my tools, and missed a number of them; I had taken the prisoner in, and lodged him, and given him a few jobs, as he was in distress - he gave himself up to the officer.</p>
               <p>Prisoner. Q.Whose tools had I when I worked for you? A.Some of mine were lent to you, but you returned them.</p>
               <p>SMITH JOBSON TAYLOR (Police-constable C 111). On the night of the 20th of April, the prisoner came to me in Regent-street, and desired me to take him into cus<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183205170107"></xptr>tody; he said he had committed a robbery some days before, and taken three saws from Nassau-street - I went there, and found it was true; the next morning I went to the prosecutor, who gave me the duplicates.</p>
               <p>
            
